29/09/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Promoting cultural diversity, peace and education was the focus of the 11th Francophony Summit, which wrapped up in Bucharest on Friday (29 September). 
State and government leaders of 63 countries participated in the event, held under the auspices of the Romanian chairmanship of the International Organisation of Francophony. 
Top officials from the European Commission, UNESCO and the African Union also attended. 
Romania is the first European country apart from France to host the summit. 
(Azi, Nine o'clock - 29/09/06; Rompres - 28/09/06)
